msg.delta: Sunrise happens when your location rotates into sunlight.
Sunset is the reverse, heading into night.

msg.message: Sunrise is when your spot on Earth rotates into daylight; sunset is the same rotation carrying you back into the planet's shadow. The colors differ because morning light travels through cooler, cleaner air, while evenings pass through dustier skies.
